They touch each other but do not intersect.
</p><p><b>Example2</b> is a valid 2-manifold because there is an intersection. Now the construct meets the 2-manifold constraint stipulating that <i>each edge  must connect exactly two facets.</i> 
</p><p>Pieces you are subtracting must extend past the original part. (<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.iheartrobotics.com/2010/01/openscad-tip-manifold-space-and-time.html">OpenSCAD Tip: Manifold Space and Time</a>, retrieved 18:40, 22 March 2010 (UTC)).
</p><p>For reference, another situation that causes the design to be non-exportable is when two faces that are each the result of a subtraction touch. Then the error message comes up.
</p>
